HEADWORD: Friday
<hw>Fri"day</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>friged⟦ae⟧g</ets>, fr. <ets>Frigu</ets>, the gooddes of marriage;
<ets>friqu</ets> love + <ets>d⟦ae⟧g</ets> day; cf. Icel.
<ets>Frigg</ets> name of a goddess, the wife of Odin or Wodan, OHG.
<ets>Fr⟦imac⟧atag</ets>, Icel. <ets>Frj⟦amac⟧dagr</ets>. AS.
<ets>frigu</ets> is prob. from the root of E. <ets>friend</ets>,
<ets>free</ets>. See <er>Free</er>, and <er>Day</er>.]</ety> <def>The
sixth day of the week, following Thursday and preceding
Saturday.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

